places.name: Narikala Fortress
places.description: An ancient fortress offering panoramic views of Tbilisi and the Kura River, accessible by a cable car.

places.name: Tbilisi Old Town
places.description: Charming narrow streets filled with beautiful architecture, cafés, and shops that reflect the city’s rich history.

places.name: sulfur baths
places.description: Famous for their natural hot springs; a perfect place to relax and experience local traditions in the Abanotubani district.

places.name: Mtatsminda Park
places.description: Located on a hill, this park offers rides, restaurants, and fantastic views of the city.

places.name: Rustaveli Avenue
places.description: The main avenue known for its theaters, museums, and vibrant atmosphere, representing modern Tbilisi culture.

places.name: The Bridge of Peace
places.description: A modern pedestrian bridge made of glass and steel, symbolizing the city's integration of tradition and modernity.

places.name: Fabrika
places.description: A trendy space that features a hostel, art galleries, and workshops, ideal for finding local crafts and enjoying street food.

places.name: Museum of Georgia
places.description: Home to a vast collection of archaeological artifacts, including the famous gold treasure of Colchis.

places.name: Holy Trinity Cathedral (Sameba)
places.description: One of the largest Orthodox cathedrals in the world, known for its impressive architecture and beautiful interior.

places.name: Lisi Lake
places.description: A picturesque lake surrounded by nature, ideal for picnics, walks, and leisure activities.

parsed.summary: Tbilisi is a vibrant blend of old and new, rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. From ancient fortresses and charming old streets to modern architecture and serene lakes, there's something for every type of traveler.
